  </figure>
  <p>Users generally see and interact with touchscreens, keyboards, and monitors, but it's the
    processors and memory that perform the actual computation. Nowadays it's fairly standard, even
    for a smartphone, to have at least eight processors and four gigabytes (four billion cells) of
    memory. </p>
